00:29:18.530 --> 00:29:20.900
A question from Faye [phonetic]:

00:29:20.900 --> 00:29:27.550
Are automated captions better
than auto-generated captions?

00:29:27.550 --> 00:29:31.510
I know custom captions are the best,
but a lot of clients aren't going

00:29:31.510 --> 00:29:31.950
to do it.

00:29:31.950 --> 00:29:35.670
So it's either
auto-generated or nothing.

00:29:35.670 --> 00:29:36.778
Thoughts.

00:29:36.779 --> 00:29:40.100
>> SANDI: Well,
I'd say auto is better than nothing.

00:29:40.100 --> 00:29:45.400
At least it gives people who
need them some sort of context.

00:29:47.570 --> 00:29:49.110
No captions leaves
them with nothing.

00:29:49.110 --> 00:29:49.770
What do they do?

00:29:49.770 --> 00:29:54.130
I don't think artificial
intelligence can help them yet

00:29:54.130 --> 00:29:56.050
in auto-generating captions.

00:29:57.060 --> 00:30:00.670
You're not going to get them
to upload a video to YouTube

00:30:00.670 --> 00:30:03.770
to get it generated or get
them to sign up for service.

00:30:03.770 --> 00:30:09.540
So I'm not sure that
nothing is the answer.

00:30:09.540 --> 00:30:11.180
It's like the progress
over perfection.

00:30:11.180 --> 00:30:12.160
It's progress.

00:30:12.160 --> 00:30:13.330
It's better than nothing.

00:30:13.330 --> 00:30:17.070
It shows that at least you
put some effort into it.

00:30:17.070 --> 00:30:22.770
And maybe you can slowly convince
people to take the time to do it.

00:30:22.770 --> 00:30:23.680
Yes, it's work.

00:30:23.680 --> 00:30:24.920
Everything is work.

00:30:24.920 --> 00:30:27.630
You just make time for
it in your scheduling.

00:30:27.630 --> 00:30:30.880
If you're putting content together
and you know there's going

00:30:30.880 --> 00:30:34.000
to be video and you know it's
going to need to be captioned,

00:30:34.000 --> 00:30:35.120
put that in your schedule.

00:30:35.121 --> 00:30:38.861
Make the time for it, and then
it just becomes second nature.

00:30:41.160 --> 00:30:41.650
>> BEN: Yes.

00:30:41.650 --> 00:30:43.690
Question from Sambor [phonetic]:

00:30:43.690 --> 00:30:46.550
Do you have any examples
of tools like Hemingway app

00:30:46.550 --> 00:30:48.490
for languages other than English?

00:30:49.700 --> 00:30:51.250
>> SANDI: Ooh.

00:30:51.250 --> 00:30:52.140
No.

00:30:52.140 --> 00:30:54.040
And that's a very good question.

00:30:54.040 --> 00:30:55.130
[laughs]

00:30:55.130 --> 00:30:57.140
Not that I know of off
the top of my head.

00:30:57.140 --> 00:31:01.700
I would think, though,
that Word, because it's got

00:31:01.700 --> 00:31:04.750
the accessibility checker in it, as
well as the reading-level checker in.

00:31:04.750 --> 00:31:07.740
If you're using it in
your native language,

00:31:07.740 --> 00:31:09.410
that might be an
alternative for you.

00:31:10.700 --> 00:31:15.970
Certainly, ChatGPT or any of those
AI tools can be a good source.

00:31:15.970 --> 00:31:21.220
As long as you're asking the right
prompt, they’ll help you get closer.

00:31:21.220 --> 00:31:24.230
They're not going to get you
perfect, but they'll get you closer.

00:31:24.230 --> 00:31:29.610
The other thing on just that
whole idea of another language is

00:31:29.610 --> 00:31:32.970
that we forget that not
everybody that's listening to us

00:31:32.970 --> 00:31:36.590
or reading our content speaks
the same language as us,

00:31:36.590 --> 00:31:38.470
or that's it’s their
native language.

00:31:38.470 --> 00:31:41.390
This is particularly important
in a learning institution

00:31:41.390 --> 00:31:44.690
where you've got students
from all over the world.

00:31:45.890 --> 00:31:48.620
You can't assume that they're
going to understand everything

00:31:48.620 --> 00:31:50.160
that you deliver in
your native language.

00:31:50.160 --> 00:31:52.830
So plain language helps.

00:31:52.830 --> 00:31:55.920
Translation tools can do a
better job of translating it

00:31:55.920 --> 00:31:59.260
to somebody's preferred
language if the language

00:31:59.260 --> 00:32:01.310
that you're using is plain.

00:32:01.310 --> 00:32:04.020
So there's that added
benefit as well.

